The Nigerian Defence Academy (NDA) has decorated with their new ranks 12 officers of the Academy who were recently promoted to the rank of Major and its equivalent in the Nigerian Armed Forces. This is just as the NDA Commandant, Major General Jamil Sarham, has challenged the promoted officers of the Nigerian Armed Forces serving in the Academy to always render selfless service while discharging their duties to the nation. The Commandant stated this at the NDA Officers Mess during the decoration ceremony. Gen Sarham lamented on unguarded utterances associated with some military personnel while encouraging the newly promoted officers to resist the urge to engage in such acts. He further urged them to double their efforts at carrying out their duties professionally, especially at this time that the nation and the world at large is faced with security challenges. To succeed in their careers, the Commandant also urged the newly promoted officers to remain steadfast and loyal to the military, stressing that they are likely to face tougher challenges ahead. The event was attended by Directors, officers serving in the Academy and family members of the newly promoted officers.